{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd00-7850-9bc2-9ed88a017dd7",
  "content": "# crates/corvia-inference/Cargo.toml\n\n## Future: vLLM and Full GPU Stack\n\nThe `cuda` toggle establishes the GPU foundation:\n\n- **`corvia-workspace enable vllm`** — future toggle that spins up a vLLM container with `--gpus all` (requires NVIDIA Container Toolkit). The `cuda` flag serves as a prerequisite.\n- **Chat model GPU acceleration** — candle's CUDA features can be gated similarly with a `cuda` cargo feature on corvia-inference.\n- **NVIDIA Container Toolkit detection** — added to status output when Docker GPU services are introduced.\n\n\n## Files Changed\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `.devcontainer/scripts/corvia-workspace.sh` | Add `enable_cuda`, `disable_cuda`, update `show_status`, update usage |\n| `.devcontainer/scripts/post-create.sh` | Update help text to mention `cuda` |\n| `crates/corvia-inference/Cargo.toml` | Add `cuda` feature |\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-04-m4.5-cuda-toggle-design.md",
